{"name": "pgliveapp", "metadata": {"name": "pgliveapp", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pglive", "pyqt6"], "summary": "Add your description here", "upload_time": 1734596812}, "documentation": ["# pgliveApp\n\nThis project is a live plotting application using PyQt6 and pglive. It allows you to create real-time plots with customizable settings.\n\n## Features\n\n- Real-time data plotting\n- Multiple plot support\n- Customizable plot titles and layout\n- UDP socket communication for data input\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the required dependencies, run:\n```sh\nuv add pgliveapp\n```\n\nUsage\nTo run the application, execute:\n```sh\npgliveapp --plots-cnt <number_of_plots> --cols <number_of_columns> --port <port_number> --ip <ip_address>\n```\n\nFor example:\n```sh\npgliveapp --plots-cnt 2 --cols 1 --port 4000 --ip localhost\n```\n\nArguments\n--plots-cnt: Number of plots to display (default: 1)\n--cols: Number of columns in the plot layout (default: 1)\n--port: UDP port to listen for incoming data (default: 4000)\n--ip: IP address to bind the UDP socket (default: localhost)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pgliveapp", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pgliveapp.app", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pgliveapp.app.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pgliveapp.app.LivePlotApp", "bases": ["QApplication"], "methods": [{"name": "pgliveapp.app.LivePlotApp.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "plots_cnt", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "plot_titles", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name"